new mailbox branches.\n- Keep the no-evidence analysis result fixed: absent new regression or drift evidence, repeated analysis-only mailbox passes are scope no-ops and should not alter the execution target.\n- Keep the no-evidence confirmation result fixed: repeated confirmation of that no-op state should not be treated as new planning signal.\n- Keep the no-evidence stability result fixed: carrying that no-op state forward is only bookkeeping, not a new plan decision.\n- Keep the unchanged-noop result fixed: when the same no-op state persists, the mailbox handoff should remain unchanged.\n- Keep the unchanged-noop carry-forward result fixed: repeating that unchanged handoff is still bookkeeping only.\n- Keep the unchanged-handoff restatement result fixed: restating the same hardening handoff does not create new mailbox scope.\n- Keep the unchanged-handoff bookkeeping result fixed: repeated explicit carry-forward of that same handoff is still non-decisional.\n- Keep the unchanged-handoff stability result fixed: the mailbox handoff remains stable until the resolver slice is actually executed.\n- Keep the unchanged-handoff carry-forward result fixed: continuing to carry that stable handoff forward is still analysis bookkeeping only.\n- Keep the unchanged-handoff boundary result fixed: that bookkeeping carry-forward still does not alter the execution boundary.\n- Keep the unchanged-handoff target result fixed: that same bookkeeping also leaves the execution target unchanged.\n- Keep the audit freeze fixed: further analysis passes should not change the resolver execution target unless a new regression or containment need appears.\n- Keep the resolver spec fixed: no further analysis narrowing is needed beyond `panel.lastPayload.dashboard.threads` unless a real regression or containment need appears.\n- Keep the remaining-gap result fixed: with no containment trigger in the current review window, the only unresolved Task 6 work is the live-thread resolver pair plus the s